{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":819,"text":"So I'm a woman with chronic schizophrenia."},{"time":2770,"text":"I've spent hundreds of days"},{"time":4579,"text":"in psychiatric hospitals."},{"time":6066,"text":"I might have ended up spending"},{"time":7871,"text":"most of my life on the back ward of a hospital,"},{"time":9698,"text":"but that isn't how my life turned out."},{"time":11898,"text":"In fact, I've managed to stay clear of hospitals"},{"time":15346,"text":"for almost three decades,"},{"time":16835,"text":"perhaps my proudest accomplishment."},{"time":18778,"text":"That's not to say that I've remained clear"},{"time":20972,"text":"of all psychiatric struggles."},{"time":22579,"text":"After I graduated from the Yale Law School and"},{"time":25004,"text":"got my first law job, my New Haven analyst, Dr. White,"},{"time":28010,"text":"announced to me that he was going to close his practice"},{"time":30595,"text":"in three months, several years"},{"time":32475,"text":"before I had planned to leave New Haven."},{"time":34172,"text":"White had been enormously helpful to me,"},{"time":36941,"text":"and the thought of his leaving"},{"time":37998,"text":"shattered me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39884,"text":"My best friend Steve,"},{"time":41354,"text":"sensing that something was terribly wrong,"},{"time":43106,"text":"flew out to New Haven to be with me."},{"time":44938,"text":"Now I'm going to quote from some of my writings:"},{"time":47026,"text":"\"I opened the door to my studio apartment."},{"time":49541,"text":"Steve would later tell me that,"},{"time":51714,"text":"for all the times he had seen me psychotic, nothing"},{"time":54450,"text":"could have prepared him for what he saw that day."},{"time":56451,"text":"For a week or more, I had barely eaten."},{"time":59124,"text":"I was gaunt. I walked"},{"time":61684,"text":"as though my legs were wooden."},{"time":63298,"text":"My face looked and felt like a mask."},{"time":66325,"text":"I had closed all the curtains in the apartment, so"},{"time":69169,"text":"in the middle of the day"},{"time":70124,"text":"the apartment was in near total darkness."},{"time":72138,"text":"The air was fetid, the room a shambles."},{"time":74890,"text":"Steve, both a lawyer and a psychologist, has treated"},{"time":78206,"text":"many patients with severe mental illness, and to this day"},{"time":81339,"text":"he'll say I was as bad as any he had ever seen."},{"time":84027,"text":"'Hi,' I said, and then I returned to the couch,"},{"time":87106,"text":"where I sat in silence for several moments."},{"time":89230,"text":"'Thank you for coming, Steve."},{"time":91075,"text":"Crumbling world, word, voice."},{"time":95126,"text":"Tell the clocks to stop."},{"time":96995,"text":"Time is. Time has come.'"},{"time":98786,"text":"'White is leaving,' Steve said somberly."},{"time":102027,"text":"'I'm being pushed into a grave. The situation is grave,' I moan."},{"time":105458,"text":"'Gravity is pulling me down."},{"time":107085,"text":"I'm scared. Tell them to get away.'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":109218,"text":"As a young woman, I was in a psychiatric hospital"},{"time":112930,"text":"on three different occasions for lengthy periods."},{"time":115434,"text":"My doctors diagnosed me with chronic schizophrenia,"},{"time":118226,"text":"and gave me a prognosis of \"grave.\""},{"time":120821,"text":"That is, at best, I was expected to live in a board and care,"},{"time":124251,"text":"and work at menial jobs."},{"time":125955,"text":"Fortunately, I did not actually"},{"time":127955,"text":"enact that grave prognosis."},{"time":129730,"text":"Instead, I'm a chaired Professor of Law, Psychology"},{"time":132571,"text":"and Psychiatry at the USC Gould School of Law,"},{"time":135196,"text":"I have many close friends"},{"time":136826,"text":"and I have a beloved husband, Will, who's here with us today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":140011,"text":"(Applause) Thank you."},{"time":146554,"text":"He's definitely the star of my show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149812,"text":"I'd like to share with you how that happened, and also"},{"time":152610,"text":"describe my experience of being psychotic."},{"time":155379,"text":"I hasten to add that it's my experience,"},{"time":157859,"text":"because everyone becomes psychotic in his or her own way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160515,"text":"Let's start with the definition of schizophrenia."},{"time":163576,"text":"Schizophrenia is a brain disease."},{"time":165797,"text":"Its defining feature is psychosis, or being"},{"time":168222,"text":"out of touch with reality."},{"time":169814,"text":"Delusions and hallucinations"},{"time":171636,"text":"are hallmarks of the illness."},{"time":173190,"text":"Delusions are fixed and false beliefs that aren't responsive"},{"time":175942,"text":"to evidence, and hallucinations are false sensory experiences."},{"time":179758,"text":"For example, when I'm psychotic I often have"},{"time":182108,"text":"the delusion that I've killed hundreds of thousands"},{"time":184359,"text":"of people with my thoughts."},{"time":185936,"text":"I sometimes have the idea that"},{"time":187641,"text":"nuclear explosions are about to be set off in my brain."},{"time":190136,"text":"Occasionally, I have hallucinations,"},{"time":192472,"text":"like one time I turned around and saw a man"},{"time":194240,"text":"with a raised knife."},{"time":195817,"text":"Imagine having a nightmare while you're awake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198609,"text":"Often, speech and thinking become disorganized"},{"time":201819,"text":"to the point of incoherence."},{"time":203365,"text":"Loose associations involves putting together words"},{"time":206244,"text":"that may sound a lot alike but don't make sense,"},{"time":209027,"text":"and if the words get jumbled up enough, it's called \"word salad.\""},{"time":211417,"text":"Contrary to what many people think, schizophrenia is not"},{"time":215855,"text":"the same as multiple personality disorder or split personality."},{"time":219270,"text":"The schizophrenic mind is not split, but shattered."}]},{"cues":[{"time":222821,"text":"Everyone has seen a street person,"},{"time":225400,"text":"unkempt, probably ill-fed,"},{"time":227423,"text":"standing outside of an office building muttering"},{"time":230000,"text":"to himself or shouting."},{"time":231813,"text":"This person is likely to have some form of schizophrenia."},{"time":234410,"text":"But schizophrenia presents itself across a wide array"},{"time":236741,"text":"of socioeconomic status, and there are people"},{"time":239565,"text":"with the illness who are full-time professionals"},{"time":242095,"text":"with major responsibilities."},{"time":244447,"text":"Several years ago, I decided"},{"time":245658,"text":"to write down my experiences and my personal journey,"},{"time":249093,"text":"and I want to share some more of that story with you today"},{"time":251391,"text":"to convey the inside view."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253054,"text":"So the following episode happened the seventh week"},{"time":255839,"text":"of my first semester of my first year at Yale Law School."},{"time":258702,"text":"Quoting from my writings:"},{"time":260907,"text":"\"My two classmates, Rebel and Val, and I had made the date"},{"time":264376,"text":"to meet in the law school library on Friday night"},{"time":267337,"text":"to work on our memo assignment together."},{"time":269621,"text":"But we didn't get far before I was talking in ways"},{"time":271423,"text":"that made no sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272946,"text":"'Memos are visitations,' I informed them."},{"time":276010,"text":"'They make certain points. The point is on your head."},{"time":278530,"text":"Pat used to say that. Have you killed you anyone?'"},{"time":280985,"text":"Rebel and Val looked at me"},{"time":283001,"text":"as if they or I had been"},{"time":284672,"text":"splashed in the face with cold water."},{"time":286252,"text":"'What are you talking about, Elyn?'"},{"time":287808,"text":"'Oh, you know, the usual. Who's what, what's who,"},{"time":290817,"text":"heaven and hell. Let's go out on the roof."},{"time":293072,"text":"It's a flat surface. It's safe.'"},{"time":294648,"text":"Rebel and Val followed"},{"time":296232,"text":"and they asked what had gotten into me."},{"time":297681,"text":"'This is the real me,' I announced,"},{"time":299544,"text":"waving my arms above my head."},{"time":301089,"text":"And then, late on a Friday night, on the roof"},{"time":303864,"text":"of the Yale Law School,"},{"time":305021,"text":"I began to sing, and not quietly either."},{"time":307313,"text":"'Come to the Florida sunshine bush."},{"time":310417,"text":"Do you want to dance?'"},{"time":311728,"text":"'Are you on drugs?' one asked. 'Are you high?'"},{"time":314203,"text":"'High? Me? No way, no drugs."},{"time":316659,"text":"Come to the Florida sunshine bush,"},{"time":319226,"text":"where there are lemons, where they make demons.'"},{"time":322499,"text":"'You're frightening me,' one of them said, and Rebel and Val"},{"time":325193,"text":"headed back into the library."},{"time":326972,"text":"I shrugged and followed them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329089,"text":"Back inside, I asked my classmates if they were"},{"time":332456,"text":"having the same experience of words jumping around"},{"time":334673,"text":"our cases as I was."},{"time":336017,"text":"'I think someone's infiltrated my copies of the cases,' I said."},{"time":340040,"text":"'We've got to case the joint."},{"time":341544,"text":"I don't believe in joints, but"},{"time":343127,"text":"they do hold your body together.'\" --"},{"time":344592,"text":"It's an example of loose associations. --"},{"time":346961,"text":"\"Eventually I made my way back to my dorm room,"},{"time":349345,"text":"and once there, I couldn't settle down."},{"time":351704,"text":"My head was too full of noise,"},{"time":353529,"text":"too full of orange trees and law memos I could not write"},{"time":357216,"text":"and mass murders I knew I would be responsible for."},{"time":359848,"text":"Sitting on my bed, I rocked back and forth,"},{"time":363193,"text":"moaning in fear and isolation.\""},{"time":365225,"text":"This episode led to my first hospitalization in America."},{"time":368352,"text":"I had two earlier in England."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370592,"text":"Continuing with the writings:"},{"time":372153,"text":"\"The next morning I went to my professor's office to ask"},{"time":374617,"text":"for an extension on the memo assignment,"},{"time":376194,"text":"and I began gibbering unintelligably"},{"time":378351,"text":"as I had the night before,"},{"time":379697,"text":"and he eventually brought me to the emergency room."},{"time":381370,"text":"Once there, someone I'll just call 'The Doctor'"},{"time":385171,"text":"and his whole team of goons swooped down,"},{"time":387138,"text":"lifted me high into the air,"},{"time":388547,"text":"and slammed me down on a metal bed"},{"time":390220,"text":"with such force that I saw stars."},{"time":392572,"text":"Then they strapped my legs and arms to the metal bed"},{"time":395130,"text":"with thick leather straps."},{"time":396797,"text":"A sound came out of my mouth that I'd never heard before:"},{"time":400143,"text":"half groan, half scream,"},{"time":402171,"text":"barely human and pure terror."},{"time":405515,"text":"Then the sound came again,"},{"time":407186,"text":"forced from somewhere deep inside my belly"},{"time":409110,"text":"and scraping my throat raw.\""},{"time":410707,"text":"This incident resulted in my involuntary hospitalization."},{"time":414986,"text":"One of the reasons the doctors gave for hospitalizing me"},{"time":418527,"text":"against my will was that I was"},{"time":419812,"text":"\"gravely disabled.\""},{"time":421219,"text":"To support this view, they wrote in my chart that I was unable"},{"time":424315,"text":"to do my Yale Law School homework."},{"time":426107,"text":"I wondered what that meant about much of the rest of New Haven."},{"time":429148,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430754,"text":"During the next year, I would"},{"time":433443,"text":"spend five months in a psychiatric hospital."},{"time":435595,"text":"At times, I spent up to 20 hours in mechanical restraints,"},{"time":439074,"text":"arms tied, arms and legs tied down,"},{"time":442564,"text":"arms and legs tied down with a net tied"},{"time":445083,"text":"tightly across my chest."},{"time":446891,"text":"I never struck anyone."},{"time":448938,"text":"I never harmed anyone. I never made any direct threats."},{"time":451844,"text":"If you've never been restrained yourself, you may have"},{"time":454618,"text":"a benign image of the experience."},{"time":457315,"text":"There's nothing benign about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459290,"text":"Every week in the United States,"},{"time":461075,"text":"it's been estimated that one to three people die in restraints."},{"time":463995,"text":"They strangle, they aspirate their vomit,"},{"time":466611,"text":"they suffocate, they have a heart attack."},{"time":468764,"text":"It's unclear whether using mechanical restraints"},{"time":471290,"text":"is actually saving lives or costing lives."},{"time":473810,"text":"While I was preparing to write my student note"},{"time":476604,"text":"for the Yale Law Journal on mechanical restraints,"},{"time":478804,"text":"I consulted an eminent law professor who was also"},{"time":481156,"text":"a psychiatrist,"},{"time":482241,"text":"and said surely he would agree"},{"time":483954,"text":"that restraints must be degrading,"},{"time":486250,"text":"painful and frightening."},{"time":487786,"text":"He looked at me in a knowing way, and said,"},{"time":489897,"text":"\"Elyn, you don't really understand:"},{"time":492226,"text":"These people are psychotic."},{"time":493964,"text":"They're different from me and you."},{"time":495485,"text":"They wouldn't experience restraints as we would.\""},{"time":498249,"text":"I didn't have the courage to tell him in that moment that,"},{"time":501083,"text":"no, we're not that different from him."},{"time":503084,"text":"We don't like to be strapped down to a bed"},{"time":505442,"text":"and left to suffer for hours any more than he would."},{"time":507772,"text":"In fact, until very recently,"},{"time":509924,"text":"and I'm sure some people still hold it as a view,"},{"time":511906,"text":"that restraints help psychiatric patients feel safe."},{"time":514938,"text":"I've never met a psychiatric patient"},{"time":517370,"text":"who agreed with that view."},{"time":518764,"text":"Today, I'd like to say I'm very pro-psychiatry"},{"time":521475,"text":"but very anti-force."},{"time":522978,"text":"I don't think force is effective as treatment, and I think"},{"time":525969,"text":"using force is a terrible thing to do to another person"},{"time":528706,"text":"with a terrible illness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":530065,"text":"Eventually, I came to Los Angeles"},{"time":532786,"text":"to teach at the University of Southern California Law School."},{"time":535284,"text":"For years, I had resisted medication,"},{"time":537604,"text":"making many, many efforts to get off."},{"time":539594,"text":"I felt that if I could manage without medication,"},{"time":542269,"text":"I could prove that, after all,"},{"time":544307,"text":"I wasn't really mentally ill, it was some terrible mistake."},{"time":547057,"text":"My motto was the less medicine, the less defective."},{"time":550364,"text":"My L.A. analyst, Dr. Kaplan, was urging me"},{"time":553452,"text":"just to stay on medication and get on with my life,"},{"time":555952,"text":"but I decided I wanted to make one last college try to get off."},{"time":559427,"text":"Quoting from the text:"},{"time":560859,"text":"\"I started the reduction of my meds, and within a short time"},{"time":564499,"text":"I began feeling the effects."},{"time":566611,"text":"After returning from a trip to Oxford, I marched into"},{"time":569452,"text":"Kaplan's office, headed straight for the corner, crouched down,"},{"time":572829,"text":"covered my face, and began shaking."},{"time":575062,"text":"All around me I sensed evil beings poised with daggers."},{"time":578217,"text":"They'd slice me up in thin slices"},{"time":580385,"text":"or make me swallow hot coals."},{"time":582027,"text":"Kaplan would later describe me as 'writhing in agony.'"},{"time":585404,"text":"Even in this state, what he accurately described as"},{"time":588489,"text":"acutely and forwardly psychotic,"},{"time":590180,"text":"I refused to take more medication."},{"time":592193,"text":"The mission is not yet complete."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594993,"text":"Immediately after the appointment with Kaplan,"},{"time":597611,"text":"I went to see Dr. Marder, a schizophrenia expert"},{"time":599909,"text":"who was following me for medication side effects."},{"time":602217,"text":"He was under the impression that I had a mild psychotic illness."},{"time":605238,"text":"Once in his office, I sat on his couch, folded over,"},{"time":608666,"text":"and began muttering."},{"time":610305,"text":"'Head explosions and people trying to kill."},{"time":612535,"text":"Is it okay if I totally trash your office?'"},{"time":615000,"text":"'You need to leave if you think you're going to do that,'"},{"time":617632,"text":"said Marder."},{"time":618615,"text":"'Okay. Small. Fire on ice. Tell them not to kill me."},{"time":621767,"text":"Tell them not to kill me. What have I done wrong?"},{"time":623415,"text":"Hundreds of thousands with thoughts, interdiction.'"},{"time":625992,"text":"'Elyn, do you feel like you're"},{"time":627727,"text":"dangerous to yourself or others?"},{"time":629224,"text":"I think you need to be in the hospital."},{"time":631639,"text":"I could get you admitted right away, and the whole thing"},{"time":633496,"text":"could be very discrete.'"},{"time":634631,"text":"'Ha, ha, ha."},{"time":636312,"text":"You're offering to put me in hospitals?"},{"time":638649,"text":"Hospitals are bad, they're mad, they're sad."},{"time":641592,"text":"One must stay away. I'm God, or I used to be.'\""},{"time":645256,"text":"At that point in the text,"},{"time":646839,"text":"where I said \"I'm God, or I used to be,\" my husband"},{"time":648744,"text":"made a marginal note."},{"time":649769,"text":"He said, \"Did you quit or were you fired?\""},{"time":651376,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":653607,"text":"\"'I give life and I take it away."},{"time":657359,"text":"Forgive me, for I know not what I do.'"}]},{"cues":[{"time":659056,"text":"Eventually, I broke down in front of friends, and"},{"time":662370,"text":"everybody convinced me to take more medication."},{"time":664878,"text":"I could no longer deny the truth,"},{"time":666824,"text":"and I could not change it."},{"time":668346,"text":"The wall that kept me, Elyn, Professor Saks,"},{"time":670995,"text":"separate from that insane woman hospitalized years past,"},{"time":674108,"text":"lay smashed and in ruins.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":676219,"text":"Everything about this illness says I shouldn't be here,"},{"time":678892,"text":"but I am. And I am, I think, for three reasons:"},{"time":681766,"text":"First, I've had excellent treatment."},{"time":684158,"text":"Four- to five-day-a-week psychoanalytic psychotherapy"},{"time":687104,"text":"for decades and continuing, and excellent psychopharmacology."},{"time":690088,"text":"Second, I have many close family members and friends who know me"},{"time":694132,"text":"and know my illness."},{"time":695386,"text":"These relationships have given my life a meaning"},{"time":697710,"text":"and a depth, and they also helped me navigate"},{"time":699877,"text":"my life in the face of symptoms."},{"time":701845,"text":"Third, I work at an enormously supportive workplace"},{"time":705013,"text":"at USC Law School."},{"time":706598,"text":"This is a place that not only accommodates my needs"},{"time":709623,"text":"but actually embraces them."},{"time":711014,"text":"It's also a very intellectually stimulating place,"},{"time":714045,"text":"and occupying my mind with complex problems"},{"time":716637,"text":"has been my best and most powerful and most reliable"},{"time":720070,"text":"defense against my mental illness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721790,"text":"Even with all that — excellent treatment, wonderful family and"},{"time":725093,"text":"friends, supportive work environment —"},{"time":727009,"text":"I did not make my illness public"},{"time":729342,"text":"until relatively late in life,"},{"time":730775,"text":"and that's because the stigma against mental illness"},{"time":733294,"text":"is so powerful that I didn't feel safe with people knowing."},{"time":735902,"text":"If you hear nothing else today,"},{"time":738318,"text":"please hear this: There are not \"schizophrenics.\""},{"time":741752,"text":"There are people with schizophrenia, and these people"},{"time":744903,"text":"may be your spouse, they may be your child,"},{"time":746998,"text":"they may be your neighbor, they may be your friend,"},{"time":749422,"text":"they may be your coworker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750846,"text":"So let me share some final thoughts."},{"time":753702,"text":"We need to invest more resources into research and treatment"},{"time":757134,"text":"of mental illness."},{"time":758374,"text":"The better we understand these illnesses, the better"},{"time":760430,"text":"the treatments we can provide, and the better the treatments"},{"time":762638,"text":"we can provide, the more we can offer people care,"},{"time":765078,"text":"and not have to use force."},{"time":766526,"text":"Also, we must stop criminalizing mental illness."},{"time":769478,"text":"It's a national tragedy and scandal that the L.A. County Jail"},{"time":773526,"text":"is the biggest psychiatric facility in the United States."},{"time":776168,"text":"American prisons and jails are filled with people who suffer"},{"time":780084,"text":"from severe mental illness, and many of them are there\n"},{"time":782568,"text":"because they never received adequate treatment."},{"time":784545,"text":"I could have easily ended up there or on the streets myself."},{"time":787974,"text":"A message to the entertainment industry and to the press:"},{"time":791198,"text":"On the whole, you've done a wonderful job fighting stigma"},{"time":795262,"text":"and prejudice of many kinds."},{"time":797078,"text":"Please, continue to let us see characters in your movies,"},{"time":800078,"text":"your plays, your columns,"},{"time":802206,"text":"who suffer with severe mental illness."},{"time":804030,"text":"Portray them sympathetically,"},{"time":805790,"text":"and portray them in all the richness and depth"},{"time":808429,"text":"of their experience as people and not as diagnoses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811956,"text":"Recently, a friend posed a question:"},{"time":814232,"text":"If there were a pill I could take"},{"time":816007,"text":"that would instantly cure me, would I take it?"},{"time":817818,"text":"The poet Rainer Maria Rilke"},{"time":820511,"text":"was offered psychoanalysis."},{"time":821983,"text":"He declined, saying, \"Don't take my devils away,"},{"time":824295,"text":"because my angels may flee too.\""},{"time":826054,"text":"My psychosis, on the other hand,"},{"time":828247,"text":"is a waking nightmare in which my devils are so terrifying"},{"time":830919,"text":"that all my angels have already fled."},{"time":832855,"text":"So would I take the pill? In an instant."},{"time":836759,"text":"That said, I don't wish to be seen as regretting"},{"time":839440,"text":"the life I could have had if I'd not been mentally ill,"},{"time":841833,"text":"nor am I asking anyone for their pity."},{"time":844115,"text":"What I rather wish to say is that the humanity we all share"},{"time":847261,"text":"is more important than the mental illness we may not."},{"time":849879,"text":"What those of us who suffer with mental illness want"},{"time":852337,"text":"is what everybody wants:"},{"time":853791,"text":"in the words of Sigmund Freud, \"to work and to love.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":856325,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":859348,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":860025,"text":"Thank you. Thank you. You're very kind. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":864818,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}